# LedgerLand Backend — Implementation Plan

Build a complete Express + TypeScript (ESM) backend for the LedgerLand blockchain-backed land registry MVP, following the [backend docs](file:///d:/Projects/LedgerLand/ledgerland%20docs/backend%20docs.md) specification.

## Proposed Changes

Work will be executed in **7 sequential phases**. Each phase builds on the previous one.

---

### Phase 1 — Project Scaffolding & Configuration

Set up the `backend/` directory with all tooling, configs, and environment defaults.

#### [NEW] backend/package.json
- Express, Mongoose, ethers v6, jsonwebtoken, bcryptjs, uuid, pdfkit, cors, dotenv
- Dev: TypeScript, tsx, Hardhat, Jest, ts-jest, supertest
- Scripts: `dev`, `build`, `start`, `compile:solidity`, `node:chain`, `deploy:local`, `test`

#### [NEW] backend/tsconfig.json
- ESM (`"module": "NodeNext"`), strict mode, output to `dist/`

#### [NEW] backend/hardhat.config.ts
- Solidity 0.8.x, Hardhat network config

#### [NEW] backend/.env
- Dev defaults for MongoDB, JWT secret, RPC URL, etc.

#### [NEW] backend/.gitignore
- `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `uploads/`, `artifacts/`, `cache/`, `.env`

